# Global Project Rules

## Design Token Rule
- Use predefined color tokens only.
- Do not use hardcoded color values in component styles.
- If a new color is needed, add it first in the token set in `:root`, then reference the token.
- Follow a 60/30/10 visual balance per screen:
  - 60% base neutrals and backgrounds
  - 30% supporting surfaces and section fills
  - 10% accents for CTA, focus, highlights
- Keep semantic colors role-locked:
  - success is green family only
  - warning is orange family only
  - danger is red family only
  - info is cyan or blue family only
- Do not use more than 2 to 3 brand hues prominently in one viewport.
- Prefer gradients/tints from existing tokens instead of introducing new standalone colors.
- Ensure accessible contrast for text and controls in all themes/sections.

## Content Punctuation Rule
- Do not use em dashes in UI copy or content.
- Use commas, colons, or full stops instead.
